main event: A sighting of an unidentified object occurred on 15 February 1955 at Alert, Ellesmere Island.
interesting points: The object was reported to have possibly been formed by aircraft., A military observation classified the object as a potential contrail., The object disappeared within ten minutes after being observed., Three weather observers simultaneously witnessed the event., The altitude of the observed formation was estimated to be between five to six thousand feet.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object, possibly a contrail
